        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 6:23PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 622 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Eckley, or 16 miles northeast of Yuma, moving
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wray.

This includes Highway 385 between mile markers 246 and 256.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM MDT for
northeastern Colorado.</instruction>
